\fs26 \cf0 This is a command line tool - from the terminal run: 'tms help' for instructions.\
Allows very basic cvs read and status operations on local Time Machine volumes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\qj
\cf0 As someone who is often in a Terminal environment I become frustrated with the Time Machine GUI and found it totally inadequate for when I needed to quickly determine what had been backed up and what had changed.\
